They are one of a kind in design, and have adaptations necessary to improve the functions of better hand placement on the magazine well. They also have over sized beveled walls all around the entry of the magazine wells to feed fast and easy. All season trigger guards have been included in the design to add additional strength and durability to the receiver.  

The Jig. This jig was engineered for those who have never machined or completed a receiver before. Simply drill four holes through the drill guide with a large 7/16" drill, to remove the majority of the material initially. Prior to installing the milling guide template, to square out the rest of the trigger control cavity efficiently. The carbide end mill is included. 

Inside the standard kit, you have a Cast Receiver with the jig and all the hardware to install it into the fixture. A carbide end mill, DVD and step by step slideshow instructions so you can understand and work at your own pace. I also provide personal technical support for this product and can vocally assist you through this procedure on site for a fee of $60 and if needed rent you a drill press for an additional $20. Providing one on one education on the drilling and milling skills is an excellent experience you can embrace for the rest of your life, and continue to produce beautifully machined receivers on your own, I grantee it! 

If you are interested in this concept feel free to contact me.

Kevin Johnson REDACTED

title: For Sale:  Winchester 94 in .30-30
postcontent:
Winchester Model 1894 in great working condition. Has the good shell lifter.

Comes with a 20" barrel and a seven-round tube. This is the old top-ejection version intended to be carried at half-cock in the field for a total capacity of eight rounds.

Spring cover / loading gate does not bind as newer specimens tend to do. This means that you can fully insert one cartridge into the tube before loading the next. More importantly, it means you can top off the magazine in the field without first emptying it.

Chambered in .30 WCF aka .30-30 aka .30/30. Serial number dates to 1975.


Also have two boxes of Winchester-brand 150-grain power-point rounds (40 rounds total) if you want either or both. $12 per box.
